               <msContents>
                  <summary> The Missal. F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-22v: Office Prayers.  F<locus target="#23r">23r, </locus>-74r: Ordinary of the Mass. F<locus target="#74r">74r, </locus>-94r: Anaphora of the Apostles, Qǝddase Ḫawaryat, ቅዳሴ፡ ሐዋርያት፡. F<locus target="#94r">94r, </locus>-99r: Anaphora of Our Lord, ቅዳሴ፡ እግዚእ፡. See Mercer.See HSEA; EMIP 27. F<locus target="#99r">99r, </locus>-111v: Anaphora of John, Son of Thunder, Qǝddase Yoḥannǝs Wäldä Nägwädǝgwad, ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27.  F<locus target="#112r">112r, </locus>-127r:  Anaphora of Our Lady Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, Qǝddase Maryam Gwäs’a, ቅዳሴ፡ ማርያም፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27.  F<locus target="#127r">127r, </locus>-138v: Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers, Qǝddase za-Śäläsǝtu, ቅዳሴ፡ ዘሠለስቱ፡ ምዕት፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27.  F<locus target="#138v">138v, </locus>-152v: Anaphora of Athanasius the Apostolic, Qǝddase Atǝnatewos, ቅዳሴ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡.   F<locus target="#153r">153r, </locus>-164v: Anaphora of Basil of Caesarea, Qǝddase Baslǝyos, ቅዳሴ፡ ባስልዮስ፡. Ff.  164v-172r: Anaphora of Gregory, brother of Basil, Qǝddase Gorǝgorǝyos, ‘Ǝḫǝwä Baslǝyos., ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ እኅወ፡ ባስልዮስ፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27. F<locus target="#173v">173v, </locus>-181r: Anaphora of Epiphanius, Qǝddase Estifanǝyos, ቅዳሴ፡ ኤጲፋንዮስ፡. Ff.  181v-188r: Anaphora of John Chrysostom, Qǝddase Yoḥannǝs Afä Wärq, ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈወርቅ፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27. F<locus target="#188r">188r, </locus>-196r: Anaphora of Cyril of Alexandria, Qǝddase Qerǝlos, ቅዳሴ፡ ቄርሎስ፡. F<locus target="#196r">196r, </locus>-203v: Anaphora of Jacob of Serugh, Qǝddase Ya’ǝkob Zä-Śǝrug, ቅዳሴ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ ዘሥሩግ፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27. F<locus target="#203v">203v, </locus>-207r:  Anaphora of Dioscorus, Qǝddase Diosǝqoros, ቅዳሴ፡ ዲዮስቆሮስ፡. F<locus target="#207r">207r, </locus>-211v: Anaphora of Gregory, the second, Qǝddase Gorǝgorǝyos Kalǝ‘, ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ ካልዕ፡, also known as Anaphora of Gregory, the Wonder Worker, Qǝdase Gorǝgorǝyos, Gäbare mänkǝrat, ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ ገባሬ፡ መንክራት፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27.  F<locus target="#52r">52r</locus> mentions bishops Matewos (1889-1926) and Qerelos (1874-1927)</summary>
